<br>
-Fix speed song dropping (affects all speed classes)<br>
<br>
-Fix damage add pulse missing<br>
<br>
-Make Skald/Minstrel/Bard health regen song worthwile<br>
<br>
-Minstrels and Skald shouts cost approx 1 power for 2 damage. All other insta DD shouts in the game (including shampion, thane, bard ...) cost 1 power for 4 damage. As minstrels and skalds are on exactly the same damage table it smells like a spreadsheet error. So reduce cost by half.<br>
<br>
- Put warden and skald damage add on a group friendly 1500 range. 700 range is a joke (oversight ?)<br>
<br>
- I would like to see DD shouts put on energy resist more than body resists. It is consistent with the way our DD looks (lightning effect), and give imho a slight increase in damage without breaking or imbalancing everything (seeing that body resist is more a priority than energy for most enemies)<br>
<br>
- Futy of the Gods is an insult the way it is designed, because not only it is crappy and useless, but shows a lack of understanding of which skald abilities are useful in RvR and which are not.<br>
<br>
-----------<br>
Non skald specific wish list<br>
<br>
- Not skald specific, but I feel it is a concern that a big part of the &quot;end game&quot; can not be enjoyed by a large number of classes, while a minority of classes have almost an unbalancing and unfair weight in those affairs (GTAEr's, PBAEr's, assassins ...): keep sieging and defending. There should be some serious thought put into making it (especially in defense) a bit more fun for characters that don't have ranged attacks.<br>
<br>
- Not really skald specific, but as discovered by the players and specified on the camelot herald, there are three broad categories of damage and hit points tables : (robed) casters, pure melees, and the rest : hybrids, support classes, healing classes, assassins, archers. There are effectively some slight differences (as stated by Sanya and proven by players), like a skald having a bit more combat skill than an assassin and a bit less hit points than a seer, but despite smallish variations, the broad categories are  accurate.<br>
What I would like is : to bump pure melees to a higher table than they are on actually, to bump &quot;melee hybrids&quot; similarly (halfway between their current table and the current pure melee table), and to keep assassins, healers and casters at the same state as they are at the moment. <br>
Whether &quot;non-fighter base class&quot; hybrids (minstrels, friars, bards, wardens ...) should stay at &quot;healer&quot; level, be bumped at the same power than melee hybrids or on a fourth intermediate table is open to debate.<br>
<br>
- a whole review of all epic armor stats for all classes. Skald epic armor stats are unappropriate, so are many of the epic armors. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/5/02 12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=384.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> typo</span><hr size=1> Champion not shampion (and not shampoo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mightymouseman>MightyMouseMan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/5/02 12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=384.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald Feedback</span><hr size=1> Issues with Current song:<br>
-  Speed Song: Occassionally will pulse off for a split second.  This gives the effect of a speed-up / slow down effect.  This was supposed to be fixed, and is happening less frequently now, but is still happening<br>
<br>
- Damage Add Song:  Occassionally when I hit a target the damage add does not always effect the swing.  This also was supposed to be fixed, but is still happening.<br>
<br>
Realm Abilities:<br>
=========================<br>
-  Mastery of the Arcane:  This supposedly only effects the lower level Run Fast song, but does not allow you to exceed the max run fast (ie. does not effect the level 43 high end run fast song).  <br>
Request:  This ability needs to effect all songs, and needs to allow you to exceed the caps, like other realm abilities allow you to do. (like Avoidance of Magic)<br>
If they do not want to fix this, they need to completely drop this realm ability from the Skalds line, it is 99.99% worthless to Skalds and results in people wasteing realm points, and unhappy customers.<br>
<br>
-  Fury of the Gods:  This is the opposite of the Cleric RA 'Bunker of Faith'.  But BoF is a much MUCH more powerful RA.  FoG and BoF should be equal to each other on opposite ends, and if each opposing group uses this ability they should effectively nullify each other.  <br>
This is currently not the case, the damage output for FoG needs to be increased to scale to counter BoF.<br>
FoG is not on the same scale as the Enchanter 'Brilliant Aura of Deflection' either.<br>
Request:  Either increase damage output, or reduce cost of the RA<br>
