<br>
- Extended keybars and bindable sprint will imho benefit fighter hybrids a lot, including skalds, who have a variety of spells or spell-like abilities plus a variety of weapons style to play with in battle. I might even dream to put a reactionary or positional style in my main hotbar <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Characters who cannot move when mezzed and stunned is good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  We will be able to mez people then use positional styles.<br>
<br>
- RPs from snaring and mezzing is good for us too.<br>
<br>
- (completely subjective, and in my humble opinion) Duels will hopefuly be a &quot;reality check&quot; for midgard classes, especially viking classes, that tend to idealize skalds fighting abilities and be actually much more vocal about &quot;overpowered skalds&quot; than both hibs and albs combined.<br>
<br>
Now somewhat of a rant about 1.54. <br>
I think Mythic did a terrible mistake when they designed realm abilities and rushed their release. It added a lot of imbalances to an already fragile RvR satus quo : such aberrations as Ignore Pain, Mastery of Concentration, Dodger for evade VII Assassins, See Hidden ... have twisted so much RvR dynamics that they should never have been created in the first place.<br>
<br>
No, I am not saying that, with all the delays <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ,alchemy and spellcrafting have been be &quot;rushed&quot;, in a sense that reciepes and such will be relatively free of bugs and that the stuff should work as intended due to careful and long testing when going live.<br>
<br>
However, I doubt very much that, like it was the case with RAs, all the implications of customisable max resists, customizable 10% chance reverse procs on every piece of armor, and a galore of charged effects/potions will have to RvR dynamics have been carefully tested and monitored in &quot;real&quot; situations for a long time enough. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roseannelottsa>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/5/02 8:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=384.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1.54 issues</span><hr size=1> Just a note Kjeld:<br>
