<br>
Already mentioned but I want to reinforce it:  Get rid of endurance usage for DDs.  Since we cannot block, parry or evade to the extent most other melee classes can, we need to be able to use our styles to compete, which requires endurance.  <br>
<br>
More than this though, the game system as it exists shows that endurance is NOT needed for us to shout, since we can do so when our endurance bar is empty.  I have never heard that our DDs do less damage when our END is gone, so logically it should not be a factor at all.<br>
<br>
My argument is both for game balance, and for greater continuity in this world. <p>Clapperoth Liefarg&lt;BR&gt;<br>
